parameter.value: calc_qty = 0 calc_price = 0 document.getHtmlElementsByAttribute('tr', 'class', 'lineitem').each{ table_cells = it.getHtmlElementsByTagName('td') qty = table_cells.get(1).asText().toInteger() unit_price = table_cells.get(2).asText().toInteger() total_line_price = table_cells.get(3).asText().toInteger() calc_qty += qty calc_price += total_line_price assert qty * unit_price == total_line_price } root = new XmlSlurper().parseText(document.asXml()) totalCols = root.depthFirst().findAll{ it.name() == "tr" }.find{ it['@class'] == 'total' }.td // slightly shorter alternative to above if you don't mind explicitly specifying tr // totalCols = root.body.table.tbody.tr.find { it['@class'] == 'total' }.td assert calc_qty == totalCols[1].text().trim().toInteger() assert calc_price == totalCols[3].text().trim().toInteger()
